But I want to.

23
00:02:34,759 --> 00:02:35,960
Do you have time for a walk?

24
00:02:38,432 --> 00:02:39,456
Just for a while.

25
00:02:41,664 --> 00:02:42,752
Don't worry.

26
00:02:43,919 --> 00:02:46,200
You've talked a lot about the characteristics
of Wings of Wind today.

27
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:47,319
And I have to go over them when I go back.

28
00:03:01,879 --> 00:03:03,439
In return for helping me apply the medicine,

29
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:05,888
I'll tell you a story.

30
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:12,960
Once upon a time,

31
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,280
a crocodile

32
00:03:18,039 --> 00:03:20,840
snatched a child from a mother's hands.

33
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:25,199
The crocodile said to this mother,

34
00:03:28,159 --> 00:03:29,312
answer me a question.

35
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:31,119
If you get it right,

36
00:03:31,119 --> 00:03:32,360
you can have your child back.

37
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,080
If you get it wrong,

38
00:03:34,624 --> 00:03:35,639
I'll eat your child.

39
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,719
The question the crocodile asked was

40
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,159
"Do you think I'll eat your child?"

41
00:03:47,599 --> 00:03:49,000
The mother's answer was

42
00:03:51,039 --> 00:03:52,160
"Yes".

43
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,560
I know.

44
00:03:59,759 --> 00:04:01,159
This is a classic crocodile paradox.

45
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,039
If the mother was right,

46
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,639
the crocodile would let her child go.

47
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,820
But the outcome of this story

48
00:04:09,820 --> 00:04:11,199
proves that the mother was wrong.

49
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,560
The crocodile will eat her child.

50
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,439
The mother is caught in a paradox.

51
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,160
So no matter how she answers,

52
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:24,960
she can't save her child.

53
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:26,208
But at the same time,

54
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,480
the crocodile is also caught in a paradox.

55
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:34,160
Because if it eats her child,

56
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,560
it proves the mother right,

57
00:04:37,519 --> 00:04:39,240
and it has to return the child to her.

58
00:04:41,639 --> 00:04:42,688
So,

59
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:46,720
the crocodile is also caught in the paradox.

60
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:50,279
When premise and action are cause and effect,

61
00:04:54,319 --> 00:04:55,759
it's easy to create contradiction

62
00:04:57,639 --> 00:04:58,688
or paradox.

63
00:05:01,759 --> 00:05:02,879
Just like us now.

64
00:05:14,959 --> 00:05:16,519
If you know this story,

65
00:05:19,279 --> 00:05:21,240
you should be able to understand my choice.

66
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,304
This is an impasse.

67
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,079
I tried hard to understand.

68
00:05:34,879 --> 00:05:37,199
However, I later realized that
what the mother did was wrong.

69
00:05:39,648 --> 00:05:40,680
So if it were you,

70
00:05:41,319 --> 00:05:42,464
what would you do?

71
00:05:46,079 --> 00:05:48,279
If it were me and my child was taken away,

72
00:05:48,279 --> 00:05:51,220
I would take a stick, drive the crocodile away,

73
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:52,680
and get my child back.

74
00:05:57,519 --> 00:05:59,120
Because when faced with the possibility

75
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:01,120
of losing a loved one, my instinct

76
00:06:03,199 --> 00:06:04,320
is to fight.

77
00:06:12,879 --> 00:06:13,879
But I'm not someone

78
00:06:14,839 --> 00:06:16,160
who acts on instinct.

79
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,600
No, you are.

80
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,879
Otherwise, why would you
help me modify the data?

81
00:06:20,384 --> 00:06:21,408
I…

82
00:06:23,808 --> 00:06:24,840
I was just…

83
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:27,399
You just wanted to finish
what you were supposed to do.

84
00:06:28,704 --> 00:06:29,792
Right?

85
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:31,800
This reason sounds calm

86
00:06:33,632 --> 00:06:34,688
and rational,

87
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:39,519
but we all know that it's just an excuse.

88
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:44,879
From your fear of danger, I felt love.

89
00:06:47,439 --> 00:06:48,544
So,

90
00:06:51,319 --> 00:06:54,279
can we listen to our heart,

91
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:57,639
and follow our instincts once more?

92
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:01,319
Don't be bound by the contradictions.

93
00:07:06,639 --> 00:07:07,680
Shen Xi,

94
00:07:10,208 --> 00:07:11,360
give me another chance,

95
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:13,079
and let's drive that crocodile away together.

96
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:27,480
The assessment is tomorrow.

97
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,759
You should go to bed early.

98
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,760
I just…

99
00:07:49,519 --> 00:07:50,839
I am afraid if I lose tomorrow,

100
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,120
I may not have a chance
to tell you all these things.

101
00:08:00,992 --> 00:08:02,112
Good night.

102
00:08:23,759 --> 00:08:26,120
Can we listen to our heart,

103
00:08:27,759 --> 00:08:29,399
and follow our instincts once more?

104
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:33,320
Don't be bound by the contradictions.

105
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:44,320
Passion and obsession

106
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,200
connect us.

107
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:49,399
But as sweet as a relationship starts,

108
00:08:50,559 --> 00:08:53,159
it can end with equal pain.

109
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,480
I thought that the paradox is unbreakable,

110
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:00,080
so I was stuck and unable to get out.

111
00:09:02,639 --> 00:09:03,959
But his instinct

112
00:09:03,959 --> 00:09:05,200
was able to break the chains.

113
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:09,759
Again and again,

114
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:11,720
we moved on our instincts.

115
00:09:13,152 --> 00:09:14,240
Fear

116
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,100
made me forget the power

117
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:18,000
brought by those beautiful moments.

118
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:21,919
But however painful,

119
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:23,919
no matter much I numb myself,

120
00:09:24,679 --> 00:09:25,720
I must admit

121
00:09:27,264 --> 00:09:28,352
that love

122
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,368
didn't disappear.

123
00:09:50,399 --> 00:09:52,000
Thank you for introducing us.

124
00:09:53,216 --> 00:09:54,240
No problem.

125
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:57,639
These years, parallel imports
have had low sales.

126
00:09:58,159 --> 00:10:00,440
Our company is also transitioning to exports.

127
00:10:01,279 --> 00:10:03,679
If we can really sell Maituo abroad,

128
00:10:03,679 --> 00:10:06,879
Ruifeng and we would have overcome a crisis.

129
00:10:15,456 --> 00:10:16,640
Mr. Anderson.

130
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:18,760
Hi, Mr. Anderson.

131
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:19,840
Hello.

132
00:10:25,519 --> 00:10:28,540
Thank you for taking the time to meet with us.

133
00:10:28,540 --> 00:10:29,568
It's my pleasure.

134
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:32,740
This is Miss Chen, CEO of Ruifeng.

135
00:10:32,740 --> 00:10:34,200
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

136
00:10:35,399 --> 00:10:38,020
I know why you came here. I know your meaning.

137
00:10:38,020 --> 00:10:41,320
But I don't want to beat
around the bush anymore.

138
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,320
It's a pity.

139
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:44,679
Because I already have been planning to give

140
00:10:44,679 --> 00:10:47,720
