200
00:14:19,279 --> 00:14:20,919
The forecast says there will be a storm.

201
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:23,799
Nick asked for your opinion.

202
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:27,120
Do you want to participate
or request a postponement?

203
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:30,440
If Mitsui doesn't want to postpone,
why would I want to?

204
00:14:31,679 --> 00:14:32,679
I'm not here to yield.

205
00:14:34,759 --> 00:14:37,000
Your past performances on rainy days were bad.

206
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:40,032
That was before.

207
00:14:40,768 --> 00:14:41,799
Things are different now.

208
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:46,464
You…

209
00:14:48,159 --> 00:14:49,440
Do you have something to say?

210
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:55,200
I do have some personal reasons.

211
00:14:58,840 --> 00:14:59,960
On the track that you'll be driving on,

212
00:15:02,399 --> 00:15:03,799
Shen Chuan scored 29 minutes,

213
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:06,000
38 seconds, and 225.

214
00:15:06,799 --> 00:15:09,120
My score was 29 minutes, 40 seconds, and 542.

215
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,840
Both are all rainy-day results.

216
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:19,520
I see.

217
00:15:20,919 --> 00:15:22,919
You want to see how fast
I could drive in the rain,

218
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,344
and then,

219
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:28,080
make me lose to you fair and square.

220
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:33,152
Quite the contrary,

221
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,639
I hope you can achieve the fastest time

222
00:15:37,799 --> 00:15:38,960
under the best conditions.

223
00:15:40,544 --> 00:15:41,632
Chuan and I

224
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:44,519
have been waiting for a new opponent
who can defeat us.

225
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:47,520
I noticed that those of you who have made
your way into the Super Grand Prix

226
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:48,679
are all seeking opponents.

227
00:15:50,759 --> 00:15:52,360
The word retreat has never
been in my dictionary.

228
00:15:52,919 --> 00:15:54,879
Who says that the best conditions
make the fastest time?

229
00:15:56,032 --> 00:15:57,056
Rest assured.

230
00:15:58,279 --> 00:15:59,488
I am Chen Mobai.

231
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,208
And that's the Wings of Wind.

232
00:16:07,279 --> 00:16:08,384
You haven't changed.

233
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:12,320
Well then, good luck.

234
00:16:20,159 --> 00:16:21,248
Chen Mobai.

235
00:16:23,039 --> 00:16:25,240
Get in the car. I have something to tell you.

236
00:16:36,399 --> 00:16:37,639
Don't tell me

237
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:42,600
you're here to persuade me to postpone.

238
00:16:47,104 --> 00:16:48,128
Quite the contrary,

239
00:16:48,759 --> 00:16:51,559
I hope you can make the decision
that goes with your heart.

240
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:53,799
Don't hesitate.

241
00:16:53,799 --> 00:16:55,080
To drive or not, it's your choice.

242
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:58,080
I just want to let you know

243
00:16:58,080 --> 00:16:59,759
you don't need to compete with anyone else.

244
00:17:01,159 --> 00:17:02,480
Your only opponent is yourself.

245
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:12,320
I've also said

246
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:15,936
that I want

247
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:18,920
to truly drive on a rainy day.

248
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:23,440
I think I've been hiding for long enough.

249
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:28,279
This time, no matter who it's for,

250
00:17:32,799 --> 00:17:33,960
I want to challenge myself.

251
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:39,279
I think my mother would be happy to know.

252
00:17:49,359 --> 00:17:50,368
The weather changes instantly.

253
00:17:51,799 --> 00:17:53,440
Every driver has different goals.

254
00:17:56,440 --> 00:17:58,279
I think the precondition for listening to fate

255
00:18:01,519 --> 00:18:02,592
is to do your best first.

256
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:05,640
So, is your end goal

257
00:18:06,519 --> 00:18:07,799
still the Super Grand Prix?

258
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:22,016
Here, take this.

259
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:27,359
You've said

260
00:18:27,359 --> 00:18:29,319
that my brother's helmet can bring you luck,

261
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:30,944
so I brought it for you.

262
00:18:33,839 --> 00:18:34,976
Perhaps,

263
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:38,319
you can really defeat the crocodile.

264
00:18:40,448 --> 00:18:41,536
Good luck.

265
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:57,240
Shaoqian.

266
00:18:57,240 --> 00:18:58,400
Are you really sure?

267
00:19:00,119 --> 00:19:02,079
Your opinion is to continue the test drive?

268
00:19:06,119 --> 00:19:08,480
Nick, it rains on race days.

269
00:19:09,759 --> 00:19:10,759
We chose them for a reason.

270
00:19:12,559 --> 00:19:13,680
They can handle it.

271
00:19:15,839 --> 00:19:16,960
And you, Shen Xi?

272
00:19:18,079 --> 00:19:19,119
What do you think?

273
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:24,920
Rain changes everything.

274
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:29,319
Wind, vision, traction.

275
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:31,359
These are not good conditions

276
00:19:31,359 --> 00:19:32,640
for our first test.

